title: Girls Cross Country Roundup: Lexington wins
text:
Girls Cross Country Roundup: Lexington wins Staff report 4:34 p.m. EDT October 17, 2015 STK Stock 
Mid Ohio Athletic Conference Blue Division 
Fredericktown was first at the Mid Ohio Athletic Conference Blue Division race (45 points), led by Rachel Tumbleson (6th, 20:20), Nichole Groseclose (8th, 20:41), Rachel Caputo (9th, 20:47), Lauren Davis (10th, 20:49) and Emily Cobb (17th, 21:31). 
Mount Gilead was second (61 points), led by Jenna Shipman (3rd, 20:02), Darcy Picker (11th, 20:50), Hannah Bush (12th, 20:51), Kelsey Snyder (18th, 21:36) and Micah James (21st, 22:01). 
Northmor was third (61 points), led by Kristen Duryea (2nd, 19:56), Samantha Peters (13th, 20:57), Isabelle Ditullio (15th, 21:14), Brooke Bennett (20th, 21:46) and Selena Cortez (22nd, 22:09). 
Highland was fifth (111 points), led by Sophia Thompson (7th, 20:34), Laura Spearman (16th, 21:17), Jena Buchholz (27th, 22:30), Jenna Brown (38th, 24:16) and Elizabeth Jensen (40th, 24:31). 
Cardington-Lincoln was sixth (165 points), led by Sage Brannon (29th, 22:51), Alicia McElwee (32nd, 23:11), Abbey Lorimer (41st, 24:38), Bailey Shafer (43rd, 24:55) and Jessica Shook (51st, 26:11). 
Mid Ohio Athletic Conference Red Division 
Galion was sixth at the Mid Ohio Athletic Conference Red Division race (134 points), led by Sari Conner (13th, 21:34), Ashlie Sallee (19th, 22:48), Megan Zeir (21st, 22:54), Lauren Huggins (42nd, 25:06) and Cheyenne Blair (45th, 25:24). 
Northern Ohio League Championships 
Shelby was second at the Northern Ohio League Championships (42 points), led by Makenna Heimmlich (2nd, 19:38), Macy Lynch (5th, 20:13), Haley Evans (8th, 20:25), Jenna Gonzales (12th, 20:52) and Kaitlyn Evans (15th, 21:01). 
Ontario was fourth (101 points), led by Anna Gregg (14th, 20:58), Arie Cox (16th, 21:11), Kylie Bittner (19th, 21:26), Nicole Cox (25th, 22:13) and Lily Lin (30th, 22:42). 
Willard was sixth (138 points), led by Emily Rothhaar (10th, 20:41), Lesley Burton (31st, 22:47), Felicia Rosvanis (35th, 23:00), Kelsey Poole (37th, 23:03) and Alyssa Strayer (23:10). 
Ohio Cardinal Conference 
Lexington was first at the Ohio Cardinal Conference meet (20 points), led by Dominique Clairmonte (1st, 19:01), Whitney Wendling (3rd, 19:52), Abby Miller (4th, 20:03), Mackenna Curtis-Collins (5th, 20:38) and Olivia Wolfe (7th, 20:56). 
Ashland was second (67 points), led by Brooklyn Duewel (6th, 20:48), Heather Jamieson (13th, 22:04), Olivia Plank (15th, 22:25), Shelby Benton (16th, 22:45) and Mackenzie Benton (17th, 22:50). 
Clear Fork was sixth (160 points), led by Emily Conrad (19th, 23:00), Makenzie Arnold (20th, 23:00), Emily Snell (32nd, 24:41), Dallen Moore (41st, 27:24) and Cassandra Vaughn (48th, 29:02). 
Madison was seventh (195 points), led by Star Lodwick (29th, 24:19), Lindsey Eckenwilder (39th, 26:39), Aleah Clow (40th, 27:11), Ariah Clow (43rd, 27:35) and Brittney McMahon (44th, 27:36). 
Mansfield Senior was eighth (217 points), led by Alexia Kemerling (22nd, 22:38), Tiara Haney (45th, 27:55), Deajah Haney (49th, 29:04), Amber Meeting (50th, 31:28) and Thea Crowley (51st, 39:07). Read or Share this story: http://ohne.ws/1LADdDL MORE STORIES
